{"header":"<h1>Module <code><span>Logs.L</span></code></h1>","type":"documentation","uses_katex":false,"breadcrumbs":[{"name":"Index","href":"../../../../index.html","kind":"leaf-page"},{"name":"soteria","href":"../../../index.html","kind":"page"},{"name":"Soteria","href":"../../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"Logs","href":"../index.html","kind":"module"},{"name":"L","href":"#","kind":"module"}],"toc":[],"source_anchor":null,"preamble":"","content":"<div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-with_section\"><a href=\"#val-with_section\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> with_section : <span><span class=\"optlabel\">?is_branch</span>:bool <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span>string <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span>(<span>unit <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>)</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span class=\"type-var\">'a</span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p><code>with_section ~is_branch name f</code> runs <code>f</code> and aggregates its log messages within a collapsible section of the log file (when logs are in HTML mode).</p><p>Sections should not be used while defining symbolic processes, as branching will cause a section to be opened once but closed several times.</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-log\"><a href=\"#val-log\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> log : <span><span class=\"label\">level</span>:<a href=\"../Level/index.html#type-t\">Level.t</a> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span><span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, unit)</span> <a href=\"../index.html#type-msgf\">msgf</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> unit</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Logs a message at a given level.</p><p>For instance, one can log the string &quot;The number is 42&quot; at level <code>Info</code> with</p><pre class=\"language-ocaml\"><code>log ~level:Level.Info (fun m -&gt; m &quot;The number is %d&quot; 42)</code></pre></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-smt\"><a href=\"#val-smt\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> smt : <span><span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, unit)</span> <a href=\"../index.html#type-msgf\">msgf</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> unit</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p><code>smt</code> is <code>log ~level:Smt</code></p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-trace\"><a href=\"#val-trace\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> trace : <span><span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, unit)</span> <a href=\"../index.html#type-msgf\">msgf</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> unit</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p><code>trace</code> is <code>log ~level:Trace</code></p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-debug\"><a href=\"#val-debug\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> debug : <span><span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, unit)</span> <a href=\"../index.html#type-msgf\">msgf</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> unit</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p><code>debug</code> is <code>log ~level:Debug</code></p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-info\"><a href=\"#val-info\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> info : <span><span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, unit)</span> <a href=\"../index.html#type-msgf\">msgf</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> unit</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p><code>info</code> is <code>log ~level:Info</code></p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-warn\"><a href=\"#val-warn\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> warn : <span><span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, unit)</span> <a href=\"../index.html#type-msgf\">msgf</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> unit</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p><code>warn</code> is <code>log ~level:Warn</code></p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-error\"><a href=\"#val-error\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> error : <span><span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, unit)</span> <a href=\"../index.html#type-msgf\">msgf</a></span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> unit</span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p><code>error</code> is <code>log ~level:Error</code></p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec value anchored\" id=\"val-failwith\"><a href=\"#val-failwith\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">val</span> failwith : <span><span><span>(<span class=\"type-var\">'a</span>, <span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Stdlib</span>.Format.formatter, unit, <span class=\"type-var\">'b</span>)</span> <span class=\"xref-unresolved\">Stdlib</span>.format4</span> <span class=\"arrow\">&#45;&gt;</span></span> <span class=\"type-var\">'a</span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p><code>failwith fmt ...</code> logs the formatted message at level <code>Error</code> and then raises <code>Failure</code> with that message.</p></div></div>"}